The article is a proclamation by President Donald J. Trump declaring June 16, 2019, as Father's Day in the United States. The proclamation acknowledges the importance of fathers and father figures in raising children and their impact on the well-being of families and communities. It highlights the role of fathers in instilling values, providing guidance, and supporting their children's growth and development. The proclamation also emphasizes the positive effects of involved fathers on children's self-esteem, education, and future success. The Trump administration expresses its commitment to promoting responsible fatherhood and supporting organizations that help fathers strengthen their relationships with their children. The proclamation calls on government officials to display the flag of the United States on Father's Day and encourages the people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies.